      <References/>
      <Content>It is also possible to understand χρηματισμός, οῦ as primarily focusing upon the communication rather than the aspect of revelation which makes known information from a divine source. Accordingly, χρηματισμός, οῦ ({D:28.40}) and χρηματίζω[a] ({D:28.39}) can be regarded as typical instances of semantic overlap between the process of revelation (that is, making known) and communication (Domain 33).</Content>
